This solution defines a helper function `divides` to check if one string can be formed by repeating another string. It then iterates from the longest possible substring of `str2` to the shortest, checking if the substring divides both `str1` and `str2`. If such a substring is found, it is returned as the result. If no such substring exists, an empty string is returned.
